      "language": "en",
      "problem_latex": "To calculate the area of a rectangle with a length of $$7$$ and a breadth of $$5$$, we can use $$7\\times 5$$. Therefore, the formula for the area of a rectangle can be summarised as:．\n(A) Area of rectangle $$=$$ breadth $$\\times $$ breadth\n(B) Area of rectangle $$=$$ length $$\\times $$ length\n(C) Area of rectangle $$=$$ length $$\\times $$ breadth",
